The course touches upon the basic concepts and research problems and history of ethnology and cultural anthropology, main research methods and major thematic areas of these disciplines (social structure, politics, economy, religion, family, gender roles, culture change, applied anthropology and ethics).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Purpose of the course is to provide an overview of the basic concepts and research problems of ethnology and cultural anthropology. Besides, the course touches upon research methods of these disciplines. After that, overview of the major thematic areas of these disciplines will be provided. To advance culturally informed analytic skills of discussion of students. To shape and support students' positive attitude towards cultural differences.  To promote creative use of social media in promoting tolerance and understanding in regard of cultural diversity. To foster students' skills for applying their knowledge of cultural differences.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course, student will be familiar with  the basic concepts and research problems of ethnology and cultural anthropology, main research methods and major thematic areas of these disciplines. Student will be able to analyse phenomena of everyday life from the standpoint of ethnology and cultural anthropology. Student is able to explain positive effect of cultural differences on development of a society. Student can use social media for creative promoting of tolerance and understanding in regard of cultural diversity. Student is able to apply in practice knowledge regarding cultural diversity.
